just_use auto_player.py

# label: EARLY (auto-player)
# role: agent tool — drives a LynRummy session via Python-native hints

Fetches state, calls `hints.build_suggestions(hand, board)`
locally, takes the top suggestion's primitives and posts each
verbatim to `/actions`. No /hint round-trip, no trick_result
on the wire — every action is a primitive.

Settles after each turn via `geometry.find_violation` /
`find_open_loc` when stacks overlap. Terminates when the deck
drops below DECK_LOW_WATER (≈10 cards) — not on "victory"
events, which are per-turn bonuses (see
`project_lynrummy_game_end_condition.md`).

## Surface

- `python3 tools/lynrummy_elm_player/auto_player.py` — fresh session.
- `--session N` — resume an existing session.
- `--max-actions N` — safety cap (default 200).

## Pointers

- Depends on: `client.py`, `hints.py`, `geometry.py` (all same dir),
  `/actions` + `/state` + `/score` endpoints in
  `views/lynrummy_elm.go`.
- Hints architecture: client-side per `project_hints_are_client_side.md`.
  Go owns wire + referee; Python owns decomposition.

## TODO

- `settle()` papers over geometry violations; the real fix is
  non-overlapping placement at emission time, not post-hoc
  move_stack. Still papering as of 2026-04-20.
- Python primitives emit no `gesture_metadata`, so agent moves
  teleport in Instant Replay. Phase 3 synthesis (linear drag
  from avg velocity) not started.
